theorem Topology.P1_closure_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure A = closure (interior A) := by
  have h₁ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := closure_mono hP1
  have h₂ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A := by
    have : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ A := interior_subset
    exact closure_mono this
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂

theorem Topology.P1_iff_closure_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A ↔ closure (interior A) = closure A := by
  constructor
  · intro hP1
    have h₁ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A := closure_mono interior_subset
    have h₂ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
      have hsub : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := hP1
      exact closure_mono hsub
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h₂
  · intro hEq
    intro x hx
    have : x ∈ closure A := subset_closure hx
    simpa [hEq] using this

theorem Topology.P1_implies_closure_subset_closure_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A → closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
  intro hP1
  have h : closure A ⊆ closure (closure (interior A)) := closure_mono hP1
  simpa [closure_closure] using h
